WEBVTT

01:46.583 --> 01:47.959
Dexter:
PREVIOUSLY ON "DEXTER"...

01:47.959 --> 01:51.125
I WAS WORKING ON MY PIECE
WITH THE BLOWTORCH,

01:51.125 --> 01:53.000
AND IT JUST CAUGHT FIRE.
I WAS SO SCARED.

01:53.000 --> 01:54.709
WE COULD ALWAYS
GET IN THE CAR

01:54.709 --> 01:56.291
AND PASS THE TIME
LIKE WE USED TO.

01:56.291 --> 01:57.875
[ LAUGHS ]

01:57.875 --> 01:59.583
YOU'RE GIVING DOAKES
TO THE PRESS?

01:59.583 --> 02:01.417
HE IS NOT YOUR MAN.

02:01.417 --> 02:02.625
YOUR CREDIBILITY
WAS COMPROMISED

02:02.625 --> 02:04.125
THE SECOND YOU FAILED
TO REPORT A PHONE CALL

02:04.125 --> 02:07.083
FROM THE SUBJECT
OF A GODDAMN FBI MANHUNT.

02:07.083 --> 02:09.000
WHO JOINED WHO
IN THE SHOWER THIS MORNING?

02:09.000 --> 02:10.125
HOW ABOUT,
IN THE FUTURE,

02:10.125 --> 02:11.458
I SET THE ALARM
10 MINUTES EARLIER?

02:11.458 --> 02:13.458
"THE FUTURE --"
I'M LIKING THE SOUND OF THAT.

02:13.458 --> 02:15.208
A WOMAN
NAMED LILA TOURNAY

02:15.208 --> 02:17.250
HAS FILED SEXUAL-ASSAULT
CHARGES AGAINST HIM.

02:17.250 --> 02:19.458
THAT FUCKING BITCH.

02:19.458 --> 02:21.208
I COULD LOSE EVERYTHING
OVER THIS.

02:21.208 --> 02:23.792
LILA, WHY CAN'T YOU
JUST LET ME GO?

02:23.792 --> 02:25.458
BECAUSE I'M
YOUR REAL SOUL MATE.

02:29.083 --> 02:30.250
NOT RITA.

02:34.458 --> 02:36.875
JESUS FUCKING CHRIST.
YOU'RE  THE BAY HARBOR BUTCHER.

02:36.875 --> 02:38.417
I REALLY HATE THAT NAME.

02:38.417 --> 02:39.291
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

02:39.291 --> 02:41.333
[ BOTH SCREAMING ]

02:41.333 --> 02:43.583
WHAT'S IT GONNA BE, MORGAN?!

02:43.583 --> 02:45.375
KILL ME NOW
OR SET ME FREE!

02:45.375 --> 02:47.166
DON'T WORRY, I'LL SEND
THE FBI YOUR WAY SOON ENOUGH.

02:47.166 --> 02:48.959
YOU'RE STILL
GONNA TRY TO FRAME ME?

02:48.959 --> 02:50.250
MISSION ACCOMPLISHED.

02:50.250 --> 02:52.250
ONE MORE NAIL
IN DOAKES' COFFIN.

02:52.250 --> 02:53.667
WE GOT HIM.

02:53.667 --> 02:55.291
SO YOU HAVE A TIP --
NOT DOAKES?

02:55.291 --> 02:56.959
OUR TARGET WAS HEADED
INTO THE EVERGLADES.

02:56.959 --> 03:01.333
WE WILL HAVE THE SON OF A BITCH
IN HANDCUFFS IN 24 HOURS.

03:01.333 --> 03:04.667
DO NOT EVER  GO
TO RITA'S HOUSE AGAIN.

03:04.667 --> 03:07.083
STAY AWAY FROM RITA.

03:07.083 --> 03:09.500
STAY AWAY FROM ME.

03:09.500 --> 03:11.083
WHETHER YOU LEAVE
ON YOUR OWN

03:11.083 --> 03:12.959
OR IMMIGRATION HAULS
YOUR SORRY ASS AWAY,

03:12.959 --> 03:14.083
I DON'T GIVE A SHIT.

03:14.083 --> 03:16.208
BUT I DON'T WANT TO GIVE YOU
ONE MORE DAY

03:16.208 --> 03:17.458
TO FUCK WITH THE PEOPLE
I CARE ABOUT.

03:20.000 --> 03:21.250
[ BEEP ]

03:21.250 --> 03:23.625
Female voice:
PREVIOUS DESTINATIONS.

03:23.625 --> 03:25.000
THEY FOUND DOAKES'
FUCKING RENTAL CAR.

03:25.000 --> 03:26.375
DID THEY FIND DOAKES?

03:26.375 --> 03:28.709
NO, NOT YET. BUT THE SEARCH
GRID'S CLOSING IN.

03:28.709 --> 03:30.542
Doakes: HEY!

03:30.542 --> 03:33.917
WHO'S OUT THERE?!
ANYBODY OUT THERE?!

03:33.917 --> 03:36.625
YOU HAVE ARRIVED
AT YOUR DESTINATION.

03:36.625 --> 03:39.000
SOMEBODY IN THERE?

03:54.041 --> 03:57.667
Doakes: HELLO?
WHO'S OUT THERE?!

04:04.333 --> 04:06.208
I NEED SOME HELP!

04:06.208 --> 04:10.333
GET ME OUT OF HERE!

04:10.333 --> 04:12.250
WHO ARE YOU?

04:12.250 --> 04:15.625
JUST OPEN THE DOOR!
I'M BEING HELD CAPTIVE.

04:26.250 --> 04:29.333
LEAVE THE MESS FOR ONCE.
WALK AWAY FROM THE MESS.

04:29.333 --> 04:31.083
YOU KNOW I CAN'T DO THAT.

04:31.083 --> 04:33.583
WE NEED YOU. LUNDY'S MOBILIZING
EVERY AGENCY IN FIVE COUNTIES.

04:33.583 --> 04:34.625
WE'RE CLOSING IN.

04:34.625 --> 04:36.625
YOU HAVE A RENTAL CAR.
YOU DON'T HAVE DOAKES YET.

04:36.625 --> 04:38.583
GOD, COME ON.

04:38.583 --> 04:40.583
I'M ONLY HELPFUL
IF THERE'S BLOOD.

04:40.583 --> 04:41.583
MAYBE WE'LL SHOOT HIM.

04:41.583 --> 04:43.792
THEN YOU'LL NEED
A PARAMEDIC, NOT ME.

04:43.792 --> 04:46.250
ARE YOU AFRAID
TO FACE DOAKES?

04:46.250 --> 04:48.917
YES, OF COURSE
I'M AFRAID TO FACE HIM.

04:48.917 --> 04:50.458
AND I HAVE DISHES TO DO.

04:50.458 --> 04:52.333
FINE, I'LL LET YOU KNOW
WHEN IT'S OVER.

04:52.333 --> 04:55.166
[ DOOR CLOSES, OPENS ]

04:55.166 --> 04:57.709
IT'S DOAKES.
YOU FUCKING HATE THE GUY.

04:57.709 --> 04:59.083
I USED TO.

04:59.083 --> 05:02.125
I CAN'T EVEN AFFORD TO THINK
OF HIM AS A PERSON ANYMORE.

05:02.125 --> 05:04.083
WOULD YOU GET GOING?

05:04.083 --> 05:06.417
I TRIED.

05:08.583 --> 05:10.542
Dexter: IF THEY FIND DOAKES
LOCKED INSIDE A CAGE,

05:10.542 --> 05:13.000
IT WILL SERIOUSLY UNDERMINE
MY FRAME JOB.

05:15.041 --> 05:17.250
I NEED TO BEAT THEM
TO THAT CABIN.

05:27.333 --> 05:28.834
WAITING OUT THERE
IN THE EVERGLADES

05:28.834 --> 05:31.458
ARE HORDES OF COUNTY SHERIFFS,
SEARCH PARTIES,

05:31.458 --> 05:33.500
AND RAVENOUS REPTILES.

05:33.500 --> 05:36.041
AND IN THIS CORNER,
WEARING DARK TRUNKS,

05:36.041 --> 05:37.959
THE MIGHTY DEXTER.

05:37.959 --> 05:39.458
[ HORN HONKS ]

05:45.166 --> 05:46.959
DRIVE MUCH?!

05:46.959 --> 05:48.792
[ HORN HONKING ]

05:51.333 --> 05:53.959
I NEED A MIRACLE.

06:01.834 --> 06:05.375
THERE'S A SWITCH
RIGHT BEHIND YOU ON THE WALL.

06:09.417 --> 06:12.041
GOD DAMN, IT'S GOOD
TO SEE ANOTHER FACE.

06:12.041 --> 06:13.625
I NEVER THOUGHT I WOULD.

06:15.583 --> 06:19.709
I'M SERGEANT JAMES DOAKES,
MIAMI METRO HOMICIDE.

06:19.709 --> 06:22.041
WHO PUT YOU IN THERE?

06:22.041 --> 06:23.208
A FUCKING PSYCHO.

06:23.208 --> 06:25.834
AND HE COULD BE BACK
ANY MINUTE.

06:27.542 --> 06:30.542
GRAB THAT KEY
RIGHT BEHIND YOU ON THE WALL.

06:30.542 --> 06:32.542
WHO IS HE?

06:32.542 --> 06:33.834
HIS NAME
IS DEXTER MORGAN.

06:35.917 --> 06:37.750
I NEED YOU
TO OPEN THIS GATE.

06:37.750 --> 06:40.625
WHY WOULD HE DO THAT --
PUT YOU IN THERE?

06:40.625 --> 06:44.041
BECAUSE I FOUND OUT THAT HE'S
THE FUCKING BAY HARBOR BUTCHER.

06:44.041 --> 06:45.709
PLEASE, JUST OPEN
THIS FUCKING GATE!

06:45.709 --> 06:48.792
HE'S...THE BUTCHER?

06:48.792 --> 06:50.834
THAT'S WHAT I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO TELL YOU.

06:51.875 --> 06:53.083
AND WHAT'S IN THERE?

06:53.083 --> 06:56.500
EXACTLY WHAT YOU THINK IT IS.

06:56.500 --> 06:59.875
IT'S EVIDENCE,
AND I SAW IT HAPPEN.

06:59.875 --> 07:02.333
I REALLY NEED TO GET
OUT OF THIS CAGE, LADY.

07:02.333 --> 07:06.834
[ SIGHS ]
POOR THING, ALL ALONE.

07:06.834 --> 07:10.542
I'M OKAY.
JUST OPEN THE GATE.

07:10.542 --> 07:12.917
NOT YOU, DEXTER.

07:15.250 --> 07:18.083
HIDING SUCH
AN ENORMOUS SECRET --

07:18.083 --> 07:20.583
WHAT A BURDEN
THAT'S GOT TO BE.

07:20.583 --> 07:23.041
NO WONDER
HE IS SO SHUT DOWN.

07:23.041 --> 07:26.417
WHAT ARE YOU,
HIS ACCOMPLICE?

07:30.542 --> 07:32.709
I'M HIS SOUL MATE.

07:41.458 --> 07:43.083
[ SIGHS ]

07:49.333 --> 07:51.166
YOU CAN'T LEAVE ME IN HERE
LIKE THIS.

07:51.166 --> 07:52.792
YOU'LL BE AN ACCESSORY.

07:52.792 --> 07:55.250
I'M NOT GONNA LEAVE YOU...

07:57.000 --> 07:58.333
...NOT LIKE THAT.

08:00.959 --> 08:02.291
WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING?

08:02.291 --> 08:04.750
WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING?!

08:04.750 --> 08:06.625
NO!
TURN THAT OFF!

08:06.625 --> 08:09.250
NO! DO YOU UNDERSTAND?!
THIS IS MURDER!

08:09.250 --> 08:10.875
OPEN THIS FUCKING DOOR!

08:10.875 --> 08:12.291
THIS IS FUCKING MURDER!

09:18.750 --> 09:22.208
HEY, DEXTER MORGAN,
MIAMI METRO P.D. FORENSICS.

09:22.208 --> 09:25.542
I'M HERE TO JOIN THE SEARCH
FOR THE BAY HARBOR BUTCHER.

09:25.542 --> 09:27.041
THE SEARCH IS ON HOLD
RIGHT NOW

09:27.041 --> 09:28.917
TILL THEY SORT OUT
THE CONFUSION.

09:28.917 --> 09:30.125
CONFUSION, HUH?

09:30.125 --> 09:31.709
YEAH.
IT'S A REAL MESS.

09:31.709 --> 09:33.375
TAKE A RIGHT AT THE FORK.

09:33.375 --> 09:37.208
PARK OUTSIDE THE LINE
OF FIRE TRUCKS.

09:37.208 --> 09:41.125
CONFUSION REQUIRES
FIRE TRUCKS?

09:41.125 --> 09:43.000
[ POLICE-RADIO CHATTER ]

09:57.709 --> 10:00.709
WHEN SOMETHING
BEYOND REASON HAPPENS,

10:00.709 --> 10:04.208
IT TURNS SKEPTICS
INTO BELIEVERS --

10:04.208 --> 10:06.625
BELIEVERS IN A HIGHER POWER.

10:09.500 --> 10:12.542
BUT WHAT KIND OF POWER
DID THIS?

10:18.583 --> 10:20.041
HOW THE HELL
DID YOU GET HERE SO FAST?

10:20.041 --> 10:22.625
I JUST GOT HERE AND TOOK
A HELICOPTER WITH LUNDY.

10:22.625 --> 10:24.375
I BROKE A LOT
OF SPEED LIMITS.

10:24.375 --> 10:26.500
AFTER YOU LEFT,
I REALIZED YOU WERE RIGHT.

10:26.500 --> 10:28.083
I DIDN'T WANT TO MISS
THE ACTION.

10:28.083 --> 10:31.458
WHAT HAPPENED?

10:31.458 --> 10:35.125
THEY THINK
A PROPANE TANK EXPLODED.

10:35.125 --> 10:37.458
HOW?

10:37.458 --> 10:40.417
DO I LOOK LIKE
A FUCKING FIRE CHIEF?

10:43.291 --> 10:46.125
DID THEY FIND A BODY?

10:46.125 --> 10:47.792
JUST BITS AND PIECES
SO FAR.

10:53.000 --> 10:56.208
WAS IT SPONTANEOUS COMBUSTION?

10:56.208 --> 10:58.750
DIVINE INTERVENTION?

10:58.750 --> 11:00.959
IF YOU BELIEVE
THAT GOD MAKES MIRACLES,

11:00.959 --> 11:03.750
YOU HAVE TO WONDER IF SATAN
HAS A FEW UP HIS SLEEVE.

11:03.750 --> 11:05.917
BUT WHEN YOU DON'T BELIEVE
IN ANYTHING,

11:05.917 --> 11:08.291
WHO DO YOU THANK
AT A TIME LIKE THIS?

11:28.792 --> 11:30.041
WE GOT A FLOATER!

12:05.667 --> 12:09.792
WE GOT LIFT-OFF
AND SEPARATION...

12:09.792 --> 12:12.917
GAPING AREAS OF...

12:12.917 --> 12:16.208
PULPIFIED TISSUE...

12:16.208 --> 12:20.000
EXTENSIVE
FOURTH-DEGREE BURNS --

12:20.000 --> 12:22.917
BIG-ASS FUCKING EXPLOSION.

12:22.917 --> 12:27.083
WHAT ELSE CAN YOU GIVE US?

12:27.083 --> 12:30.166
THESE LINEAR LINES
AROUND HIS EYES ARE UNBURNED.

12:30.166 --> 12:34.291
HE WAS SQUINTING --
ALIVE WHEN IT HAPPENED.

12:34.291 --> 12:35.959
WHAT ELSE?

12:38.083 --> 12:39.875
TEETH ARE INTACT.

12:39.875 --> 12:42.542
DENTAL RECORDS SHOULD GIVE US
A POSITIVE I.D.

12:42.542 --> 12:44.917
GODDAMN IT, MASUKA.
IS IT DOAKES?

12:44.917 --> 12:49.417
MALE, AFRICAN-AMERICAN,

12:49.417 --> 12:52.291
ABOUT
THE RIGHT LENGTH TORSO,

12:52.291 --> 12:55.583
HEAVILY MUSCLED.

12:55.583 --> 12:57.083
I THINK IT'S HIM.

13:02.083 --> 13:04.291
THESE ARE
THE SAME KIND OF TOOLS

13:04.291 --> 13:06.291
THAT SCUBA-DIVE CLASS
FOUND.

13:06.291 --> 13:09.500
HE'D NEED THEM
TO MAKE CUTS THAT CLEAN.

13:09.500 --> 13:11.583
THOSE COME
FROM THE SUSPECT?

13:11.583 --> 13:14.458
NO, THEY BELONG
TO A SECOND BODY.

13:14.458 --> 13:15.959
AND WHOEVER HE WAS,

13:15.959 --> 13:18.875
HE WAS DEAD AND DISMEMBERED
BEFORE THE EXPLOSION.

13:18.875 --> 13:21.417
SO THIS IS WHERE THE BUTCHER
DID HIS DIRTY WORK.

13:21.417 --> 13:23.542
IT'S A PERFECT LOCATION
FOR A KILL ROOM.

13:23.542 --> 13:25.542
IT DOESN'T GET ANY MORE REMOTE
THAN THIS.

13:25.542 --> 13:27.458
NO, IT COULDN'T.

13:27.458 --> 13:29.125
THIS IS GOOD NEWS,
GENTLEMEN.

13:29.125 --> 13:30.875
AND LADY.

13:30.875 --> 13:31.875
RIGHT.

13:31.875 --> 13:33.875
ALL RIGHT,
WE KEEP THE SEARCH ON

13:33.875 --> 13:36.583
TILL WE GET A FIRM I.D.
ON THAT BODY IN THE WATER.

13:39.208 --> 13:41.583
YOU AGREE WITH THEM?

13:41.583 --> 13:44.542
THE EVIDENCE IS
COMPELLING --

13:44.542 --> 13:46.834
OVERWHELMING, ACTUALLY.

13:49.375 --> 13:52.291
I GUESS WE GOT OUR MAN.

13:52.291 --> 13:54.750
OH, SHIT.
LaGUERTA'S HERE.

13:56.500 --> 13:58.542
LIEUTENANT...UH...

13:58.542 --> 14:01.834
I WOULDN'T
IF I WERE YOU.

14:01.834 --> 14:05.083
IS IT JAMES?

14:05.083 --> 14:08.250
THEY DON'T KNOW YET.

14:08.250 --> 14:10.917
APPARENTLY MIRACLES
ARE SUBJECTIVE.

14:10.917 --> 14:13.417
I CAN'T EXACTLY
FEEL LaGUERTA'S PAIN,

14:13.417 --> 14:15.208
BUT I CAN APPRECIATE IT.

14:15.208 --> 14:17.500
DOAKES WASN'T SO BAD
IN THE END.

14:17.500 --> 14:19.166
BUT THE TRULY TRAGIC THING

14:19.166 --> 14:21.834
WOULD BE TO LET HIS SACRIFICE
GO TO WASTE.

14:21.834 --> 14:25.166
THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY I CAN
THINK OF TO HONOR HIM.

14:25.166 --> 14:26.959
I HAVE TO EMBRACE MY FREEDOM.

14:29.291 --> 14:31.458
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

14:39.834 --> 14:42.750
SLEEP -- WHAT A CONCEPT.

14:44.542 --> 14:47.375
I CAN'T BELIEVE I ACTUALLY
CONTEMPLATED TURNING MYSELF IN.

14:51.542 --> 14:54.875
THIS IS SO MUCH BETTER
THAN A PRISON CELL.

14:59.959 --> 15:03.041
I CAN SQUEEZE
FRESH ORANGE JUICE...

15:03.041 --> 15:05.583
SAVOR A FINE FRENCH ROAST...

15:09.375 --> 15:12.291
...GRAB A MORNING WORKOUT.

15:12.291 --> 15:15.208
OKAY, WORKING OUT I COULD HAVE
DONE IN PRISON, BUT STILL...

15:17.500 --> 15:19.750
...I'M FREE.

15:33.959 --> 15:35.291
DEXTER?

15:35.291 --> 15:36.291
SORRY.

15:36.291 --> 15:38.250
HOPE I DIDN'T SCARE YOU.

15:38.250 --> 15:40.333
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
OUT THERE?

15:40.333 --> 15:43.166
WELL, I FIGURED THE KIDS
WERE STILL ASLEEP.

15:43.166 --> 15:45.500
I DIDN'T WANT
TO RING THE BELL.

15:45.500 --> 15:48.959
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

15:48.959 --> 15:52.750
WELL, I FIGURED THE KIDS
WERE STILL ASLEEP.

15:52.750 --> 15:56.625
[ LAUGHTER ]

16:03.792 --> 16:06.000
[ MOANING ]

16:19.583 --> 16:23.125
THAT WAS...UNEXPECTED.

16:25.125 --> 16:28.709
YEAH, I WOUND UP WITH SOME
UNEXPECTED TIME ON MY HANDS.

16:28.709 --> 16:32.625
LIKE 20 YEARS TO LIFE.

16:32.625 --> 16:37.041
I DON'T KNOW IF THIS IS
A GOOD IDEA, DEXTER.

16:37.041 --> 16:41.750
I WAS JUST GETTING USED TO YOU
FROM A DISTANCE.

16:41.750 --> 16:46.500
I KNOW. YOU'VE BEEN
LIKE A MIRAGE.

16:46.500 --> 16:48.083
I'VE BEEN RIGHT HERE.

16:48.083 --> 16:51.375
YOU'RE THE ONE
THAT WENT AWAY.

16:51.375 --> 16:55.667
YEAH, I DID.

16:55.667 --> 16:57.542
I KIND OF FORGOT WHO I WAS.

17:00.542 --> 17:03.125
I GOT IT STRAIGHT NOW.

17:03.125 --> 17:05.500
KEEP IT STRAIGHT,

17:05.500 --> 17:08.333
OR I WON'T BE HERE
NEXT TIME.

17:08.333 --> 17:10.000
I KNOW THAT.

17:12.500 --> 17:14.625
Astor: MOM!

17:14.625 --> 17:16.792
IT'S THE SEX POLICE.

17:19.709 --> 17:21.834
HOW COME
YOU'RE STILL IN BED?

17:21.834 --> 17:23.709
I OVERSLEPT.

17:23.709 --> 17:26.709
WILL YOU MAKE US
PANCAKES, PLEASE?

17:26.709 --> 17:28.291
WHAT'S UNDER THERE?

17:28.291 --> 17:29.834
UM...

17:32.166 --> 17:33.667
OW.

17:34.542 --> 17:38.166
[ LAUGHS ]

17:38.166 --> 17:39.417
HI.

17:39.417 --> 17:40.542
HI, DEXTER.

17:42.375 --> 17:44.709
ARE YOU GUYS
BACK TOGETHER?

17:44.709 --> 17:47.875
[ SIGHS ]
I GUESS WE ARE.

17:47.875 --> 17:49.834
[ LAUGHS ]

18:12.875 --> 18:18.291
OVER, UNDER, OVER, UNDER.

18:18.291 --> 18:20.250
MAYBE I SHOULD DO IT MYSELF.

18:20.250 --> 18:21.542
NO, I WANT TO DO IT.

18:21.542 --> 18:22.917
WE'RE GONNA BE LATE.

18:22.917 --> 18:24.875
SO WHAT?
THE CASE IS CLOSING.

18:24.875 --> 18:27.750
I KNOW. WE STILL NEED
CONFIRMATION ON DOAKES' BODY.

18:27.750 --> 18:29.375
AND IF IT'S HIM?

18:29.375 --> 18:30.875
THEN IT'S OVER.

18:30.875 --> 18:32.375
THE CASE,
NOT US, RIGHT?

18:32.375 --> 18:35.375
WE STILL HAVE
THE WRAP-UP TO DO --

18:35.375 --> 18:39.166
CATALOGUING, CONFIRMING,
FILING, MORE FILING.

18:39.166 --> 18:40.583
SO WE'VE GOT TIME?

18:40.583 --> 18:42.041
PLENTY.

18:50.959 --> 18:52.750
TIME ENOUGH
FOR A VACATION?

18:52.750 --> 18:54.041
NOW YOU'RE TALKING.

18:54.041 --> 18:57.458
TOES IN THE SAND,
TEQUILA,

18:57.458 --> 18:59.333
LITTLE, TEENY BIKINI.

19:00.458 --> 19:02.750
HOW ABOUT A PARKA?

19:02.750 --> 19:04.291
A WHAT?

19:04.291 --> 19:06.166
I'VE HAD MY FILL
OF HEAT --

19:06.166 --> 19:08.041
NO MORE HEAT.

19:08.041 --> 19:10.917
YOU'D LOOK GREAT
IN A PARKA.

19:10.917 --> 19:13.667
EVER HEARD
OF LAKE IPPERWASH?

19:13.667 --> 19:15.959
CAN'T SAY THAT I HAVE.

19:15.959 --> 19:19.083
WONDERFUL ICE FISHING --
VERY ROMANTIC.

19:19.083 --> 19:21.709
FINE, BOOK IT.

19:21.709 --> 19:24.166
LET'S JUST GO.

19:26.625 --> 19:27.792
[ ELEVATOR DINGS ]

19:27.792 --> 19:28.834
Man: MORNING, DEX.

19:28.834 --> 19:30.417
DOUGHNUT?

19:30.417 --> 19:32.917
I'M NOT REALLY FEELING LIKE
DOUGHNUTS. KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

19:32.917 --> 19:34.959
UH, NO.

19:38.667 --> 19:41.333
OH, RIGHT.

19:41.333 --> 19:43.291
[ ELEVATOR DINGS ]

19:43.291 --> 19:44.959
MMM, DOUGHNUTS.

19:44.959 --> 19:46.542
HEY, ARE YOU FREE?

19:46.542 --> 19:48.959
OH, VINCE,
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.
GOOD.

19:48.959 --> 19:51.125
I GOT A DOZEN BOXES
OF BURNT-UP SHIT FROM THE CABIN

19:51.125 --> 19:52.458
THAT NEED CATALOGUING --
COME ON.

19:59.208 --> 20:00.333
LIEUTENANT.

20:00.333 --> 20:03.333
SPECIAL AGENT LUNDY,
I WAS JUST LOOKING MORE CLOSELY

20:03.333 --> 20:06.083
AT THE DATES OF JAMES'
SPECIAL FORCES' MISSIONS, AND --

20:06.083 --> 20:08.083
WE HAVE A POSITIVE I.D.
ON THE BODY.

20:08.083 --> 20:10.375
AND THERE MAY BE
AN ADDITIONAL DATE,

20:10.375 --> 20:12.208
WHICH PUTS HIM
OUT OF THE COUNTRY --

20:12.208 --> 20:15.000
THE BURN VICTIM IS
SERGEANT DOAKES.

20:15.000 --> 20:17.667
DENTAL RECORDS
CONFIRMED IT.

20:23.667 --> 20:26.041
AND THE OTHER BODY?

20:26.041 --> 20:28.208
JOSE GARZA,
A MURDER FUGITIVE

20:28.208 --> 20:31.375
WHO'S BEEN LIVING
UNDER THE ALIAS CHRIS HARLOW.

20:31.375 --> 20:33.375
THE BODY WAS DISMEMBERED,

20:33.375 --> 20:36.208
CONSISTENT
WITH OUR OTHER VICTIMS.

20:36.208 --> 20:39.917
DEPUTY DIRECTOR ADAMS
IS CLOSING THE CASE.

20:39.917 --> 20:42.125
I SEE.

20:42.125 --> 20:46.083
LIEUTENANT...
ALL THE EVIDENCE

20:46.083 --> 20:49.375
POINTS TO JAMES DOAKES
AS THE BAY HARBOR BUTCHER...

20:49.375 --> 20:51.166
CONCLUSIVELY.

20:54.083 --> 20:55.625
I WANTED YOU
TO HEAR IT FROM ME FIRST.

20:55.625 --> 20:57.500
THANK YOU.

20:57.500 --> 20:59.792
I'M TRULY SORRY.

21:09.750 --> 21:11.542
[ SOBBING ]

21:22.041 --> 21:24.125
I DON'T KNOW
WHY THEY KEEP

21:24.125 --> 21:26.417
HAULING CRAP FROM THE CABIN
IN HERE.

21:26.417 --> 21:29.125
WE ALREADY KNOW
WHAT WE NEED TO KNOW.

21:29.125 --> 21:31.125
DOAKES
WAS A SUICIDAL MANIAC.

21:31.125 --> 21:33.959
I BELIEVE THE TERM
IS HOMICIDAL MANIAC,

21:33.959 --> 21:35.333
NOT THAT I'M JUDGING.

21:35.333 --> 21:36.500
YEAH, WHATEVER, MORGAN.

21:36.500 --> 21:38.917
HE BLEW HIMSELF UP.
THAT'S ALL I'M SAYING.

21:38.917 --> 21:40.458
I THOUGHT
I HEARD SOMEBODY SAY

21:40.458 --> 21:42.583
THE EXPLOSION WAS
A PROPANE ACCIDENT.

21:42.583 --> 21:45.834
RIGHT -- DOAKES ACCIDENTALLY
TURNED ON THE PROPANE VALVE,

21:45.834 --> 21:48.542
AND THEN HE ACCIDENTALLY
TURNED THE STOVE ON.

21:48.542 --> 21:49.750
THE STOVE WAS ON?

21:49.750 --> 21:52.291
IT WAS IN THE OFFICIAL
FIRE INVESTIGATOR'S REPORT

21:52.291 --> 21:54.458
THIS MORNING.

21:54.458 --> 21:56.375
I MEAN, I GUESS IT COULD BE

21:56.375 --> 22:00.125
THAT DOAKES DIDN'T REALIZE
FIRE AND GAS ARE A BAD COMBO,

22:00.125 --> 22:03.125
BUT MY MONEY'S
ON SUICIDE.

22:03.125 --> 22:07.542
A BADASS LIKE DOAKES WOULD
RATHER BURN THAN GET BURNED.

22:07.542 --> 22:09.959
THAT'S A GOOD LINE
FOR MY MOVIE.

22:09.959 --> 22:11.709
I BETTER WRITE IT DOWN.

22:11.709 --> 22:13.959
YOU'RE WRITING A MOVIE
ABOUT DOAKES?

22:13.959 --> 22:14.792
LIKE YOU'RE NOT.

22:14.792 --> 22:16.750
HE'D RATHER BURN
THAN GET BURNED.

22:16.750 --> 22:18.500
HE'D RATHER BURN
THAN GET BURNED.

22:18.500 --> 22:20.542
HE'D RATHER BURN
THAN GET BURNED.

22:44.041 --> 22:45.417
Rita:
I JUST CHECKED.

22:45.417 --> 22:47.667
I DIDN'T SEE ANY GPS DEVICE
IN THE MINIVAN, DEXTER.

22:47.667 --> 22:50.000
Did you check
the glove box?

22:50.000 --> 22:51.583
It's gray, rectangular.

22:51.583 --> 22:53.667
IT'S ABOUT THE SIZE
OF A PAPERBACK BOOK.

22:53.667 --> 22:55.583
No, it wasn't there.

22:55.583 --> 22:58.500
I EVEN LOOKED UNDER THE SEATS.
DO YOU THINK SOMEONE STOLE IT?

22:58.500 --> 22:59.542
Maybe.

22:59.542 --> 23:01.667
THANKS, RITA.
I'LL SEE YOU TONIGHT.

23:01.667 --> 23:03.583
IF SOMEONE STOLE MY GPS,

23:03.583 --> 23:06.625
IT WOULD HAVE LED THEM
STRAIGHT TO DOAKES.

23:06.625 --> 23:10.041
WHO DO I KNOW
WITH A NASTY HABIT OF STEALING?

23:10.041 --> 23:14.166
LILA -- MY MIRACLE WORKER.

23:21.041 --> 23:24.792
IT LOOKS PEACEFUL
IN THERE.

23:24.792 --> 23:28.291
DOESN'T IT?

23:28.291 --> 23:31.875
I'M GLAD YOU CALLED.

23:31.875 --> 23:35.917
I WAS AFRAID
MAYBE YOU'D LEFT TOWN.

23:35.917 --> 23:38.375
IT SEEMS I FOUND
A GOOD REASON TO STAY.

23:38.375 --> 23:40.083
LIKE WHAT?

23:40.083 --> 23:42.875
A NEW VICTIM?

23:47.333 --> 23:49.458
YOU MEAN YOU?

23:54.959 --> 23:57.041
THAT'S WHY YOU ASKED

23:57.041 --> 23:59.667
TO MEET AT THE AQUARIUM,
IN A PUBLIC PLACE?

23:59.667 --> 24:01.583
YOU THOUGHT I WAS GONNA...

24:01.583 --> 24:04.917
WHAT, SLIP MY NEEDLE
INTO YOUR NECK?

24:04.917 --> 24:06.917
IS THAT HOW YOU DO IT?

24:08.959 --> 24:11.208
IT'S ONE OF THE WAYS.

24:17.750 --> 24:19.542
[ SIGHS ]

24:25.166 --> 24:29.000
YOU'RE AFRAID OF ME NOW,
AREN'T YOU?

24:29.000 --> 24:33.542
I'VE ALWAYS BEEN AFRAID
OF YOU, DEXTER.

24:33.542 --> 24:35.250
WHY?

24:35.250 --> 24:37.625
FROM THE FIRST TIME
I SAW YOU,

24:37.625 --> 24:41.583
I COULD SEE HOW HOPELESSLY
CONSUMED YOU WERE BY YOUR NEED.

24:46.041 --> 24:47.583
YOU LIED TO ME.

24:50.083 --> 24:52.417
ALL THAT TIME
AS MY SPONSOR,

24:52.417 --> 24:54.291
YOU SAID ALL YOU WANTED

24:54.291 --> 24:57.458
WAS TO HELP ME CONTROL
MY ADDICTION.

24:57.458 --> 24:58.959
WE DID CONTROL IT.

24:58.959 --> 25:02.625
BUT THAT'S NOT WHAT YOU
REALLY WANTED, WAS IT?

25:06.208 --> 25:09.000
WHAT DO YOU THINK
I WANTED?

25:09.000 --> 25:11.500
TO KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE

25:11.500 --> 25:16.667
TO FEEL SOMETHING
THAT DEEPLY --

25:16.667 --> 25:18.959
ANYTHING.

25:18.959 --> 25:21.709
THAT'S WHY YOU HANG OUT
IN RECOVERY GROUPS.

25:21.709 --> 25:23.750
YOU'RE EMOTIONALLY
COLOR-BLIND.

25:23.750 --> 25:25.417
YOU USE THE RIGHT WORDS,

25:25.417 --> 25:27.583
YOU PANTOMIME
THE RIGHT BEHAVIOR,

25:27.583 --> 25:29.667
BUT THE FEELINGS
NEVER COME TO PASS.

25:29.667 --> 25:32.542
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

25:32.542 --> 25:35.375
IT IS, LILA.

25:35.375 --> 25:38.875
YOU KNOW THE DICTIONARY
DEFINITION OF EMOTIONS --

25:38.875 --> 25:41.166
LONGING, JOY, SORROW --

25:41.166 --> 25:43.458
BUT YOU HAVE NO IDEA

25:43.458 --> 25:46.125
WHAT ANY OF THOSE THINGS
ACTUALLY FEEL LIKE.

25:46.125 --> 25:49.041
YOU'RE WRONG.
I HAVE FEELINGS FOR YOU.

25:49.041 --> 25:50.959
YOU WANT TO HAVE FEELINGS
FOR ME.

25:50.959 --> 25:53.417
BUT THEY'RE
JUST IMPULSES.
ENOUGH.

25:53.417 --> 25:56.333
THEY'RE PRIMITIVE RESPONSES
TO IMMEDIATE NEEDS.
STOP IT.

25:56.333 --> 25:58.959
YOU KNOW ALL THE WORDS,
BUT YOU CAN'T HEAR THE MUSIC.
DON'T DO THIS.

25:58.959 --> 26:00.375
LILA...

26:03.875 --> 26:06.208
...I'M JUST LIKE YOU.

26:15.208 --> 26:17.583
HEY!

26:17.583 --> 26:19.500
[ GIGGLES ]

26:27.250 --> 26:30.208
I WAS DOWN
TO MY LAST HOPE.

26:30.208 --> 26:33.917
SO WAS I.

26:33.917 --> 26:36.583
WHEN HE TOLD ME
WHO YOU ARE,

26:36.583 --> 26:40.208
I THOUGHT THAT WAS
A SECRET WORTH PROTECTING.

26:40.208 --> 26:41.750
MOST DEFINITELY.

26:41.750 --> 26:45.083
I WISH YOU COULD
HAVE SEEN IT, DEXTER.

26:45.083 --> 26:47.458
THE EXPLOSION WAS...

26:47.458 --> 26:49.917
BRILLIANT.

26:49.917 --> 26:52.583
I'M MORE LIKE MY FATHER
THAN I EVER IMAGINED.

26:52.583 --> 26:54.458
I'VE CREATED A MONSTER
OF MY OWN.

26:54.458 --> 26:56.750
[ LAUGHS ]

26:56.750 --> 26:57.875
TOLD YOU.

27:00.125 --> 27:02.208
WE WERE MEANT
TO BE TOGETHER.

27:02.208 --> 27:05.208
[ SIGHS ]

27:05.208 --> 27:08.625
LILA, I'M SORRY
I PUSHED YOU AWAY.

27:08.625 --> 27:10.917
Shh.

27:11.959 --> 27:15.458
I KNOW HOW FRIGHTENING
IT MUST HAVE BEEN FOR YOU,

27:15.458 --> 27:18.667
ME SCRATCHING TO GET IN.

27:18.667 --> 27:20.542
BUT IT'S OKAY.

27:20.542 --> 27:25.000
I'M IN NOW,
AND I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

27:25.000 --> 27:26.792
I AM.

27:26.792 --> 27:29.458
EVEN WITH DOAKES GONE,

27:29.458 --> 27:32.000
I'M STARTING TO THINK
IT'S TOO DANGEROUS FOR ME HERE.

27:32.000 --> 27:33.667
I NEED TO MOVE ON,
DISAPPEAR.

27:33.667 --> 27:35.417
I'VE ALREADY SAID
MY GOODBYES.

27:35.417 --> 27:37.834
LET ME COME WITH YOU.

27:37.834 --> 27:39.875
I WAS HOPING
YOU'D SAY THAT.

27:39.875 --> 27:42.125
OH.

27:42.125 --> 27:43.625
HOW LONG
WOULD IT TAKE YOU

27:43.625 --> 27:45.333
TO GET READY?

27:45.333 --> 27:48.125
TO CLOSE MY ACCOUNTS...

27:50.500 --> 27:53.583
...SHUT UP MY BUSINESS...

27:53.583 --> 27:57.291
[ LAUGHS ]
TOMORROW AFTERNOON.

27:57.291 --> 27:59.250
GO HOME AND PACK.

27:59.250 --> 28:00.792
I'LL CALL YOU TOMORROW.

28:04.333 --> 28:06.375
MMM.

28:08.208 --> 28:10.875
I CAN'T WAIT TO GO AWAY
WITH YOU, DEXTER.

28:16.166 --> 28:17.875
I CAN'T WAIT.

28:22.750 --> 28:26.291
YOU'RE GOING AWAY WITH ME,
ALL RIGHT...

28:26.291 --> 28:28.291
IN A GARBAGE BAG.

28:30.625 --> 28:33.291
Debra:
BUT IT WENT ALL RIGHT?

28:33.291 --> 28:36.208
SURE, FOR AN INTERNAL AFFAIRS
INVESTIGATION.

28:36.208 --> 28:40.166
I SPENT TWO HOURS SAYING, "NO,
I DID NOT RAPE LILA TOURNAY.

28:40.166 --> 28:42.500
SHE'S BAT SHIT,
NUTS, WACKO."

28:42.500 --> 28:44.208
I STARTED TO RUN OUT
OF ADJECTIVES.

28:44.208 --> 28:45.667
WELL, I GOT A FEW
YOU CAN USE.

28:45.667 --> 28:48.542
THE GOOD NEWS IS THE DEPARTMENT
IS DYING TO DROP THE CHARGE.

28:48.542 --> 28:51.458
THEY'RE DODGING ENOUGH BULLETS
WITH THIS WHOLE DOAKES THING.

28:51.458 --> 28:53.333
GOOD --
SO WHEN THEY FIND OUT

28:53.333 --> 28:56.750
YOUR SO-CALLED VICTIM FLED
MIAMI, YOU'LL BE REINSTATED.

28:56.750 --> 28:58.208
LILA WENT AWAY?

28:58.208 --> 28:59.625
SHE FUCKING BETTER.

28:59.625 --> 29:01.041
I DROPPED BY HER HOUSE
LAST NIGHT

29:01.041 --> 29:02.792
AND TOLD HER TO HAUL
HER SLAG ASS OUT OF TOWN

29:02.792 --> 29:04.375
BEFORE SHE'S DEPORTED.

29:04.375 --> 29:05.500
YOU DID THAT FOR ME?

29:05.500 --> 29:08.166
OF COURSE --
FOR YOU AND FOR DEX.

29:09.875 --> 29:13.250
YOU TWO WINDOW-LICKERS NEEDED
SOMEBODY TO SNAP YOU OUT OF IT.

29:13.250 --> 29:15.417
IT'S GOOD TO KNOW

29:15.417 --> 29:17.917
SOMEBODY'S PULLING FOR YOU
WHEN YOU'RE DOWN.

29:19.750 --> 29:23.083
OKAY, I GET THE POINT.

29:23.083 --> 29:24.583
ARE YOU SURE
LILA GOT THE MESSAGE?

29:24.583 --> 29:26.083
YEAH, TOTALLY.

29:26.083 --> 29:30.542
I MEAN,
I MADE IT PRETTY CLEAR.

29:30.542 --> 29:32.458
EXCUSE ME.

29:32.458 --> 29:35.125
DONATIONS CAN BE MADE
DIRECTLY TO ME.

29:35.125 --> 29:36.667
DONATIONS?

29:36.667 --> 29:39.583
FOR SERGEANT DOAKES'
MEMORIAL SERVICE.

29:39.583 --> 29:41.083
YOU GOT TO BE KIDDING?

29:41.083 --> 29:44.041
IT'S WHAT WE DO
FOR A FELLOW OFFICER.

29:46.291 --> 29:48.166
THANKS AGAIN, MORGAN.

29:48.166 --> 29:51.333
YEAH.

29:51.333 --> 29:53.125
EXCUSE ME, LIEUTENANT.

29:53.125 --> 29:57.083
I, UM...WAS WONDERING --

29:57.083 --> 29:59.125
UH, CHECKS PAYABLE TO CASH.

29:59.125 --> 30:01.709
ACTUALLY I JUST WANTED
TO OFFER MY SUPPORT...

30:01.709 --> 30:04.959
SYMPATHY...

30:04.959 --> 30:07.625
OR WHATEVER THE FUCK --
IF YOU WANT TO TALK.

30:07.625 --> 30:10.417
THANK YOU, MORGAN.
I CAN MANAGE.

30:10.417 --> 30:12.083
I'M NOT SO SURE.

30:12.083 --> 30:15.041
I MEAN, YOU'RE COLLECTING MONEY
TO HONOR A KILLER.

30:15.041 --> 30:17.125
I'M NOT HONORING
THE BUTCHER.

30:17.125 --> 30:18.834
I'M HONORING
JAMES DOAKES.

30:21.041 --> 30:23.583
RESPECTFULLY, MARIA,
THAT'S DENIAL.

30:23.583 --> 30:24.625
SO IT IS.

30:24.625 --> 30:26.458
YOU'RE CHOOSING
TO BE IN DENIAL?

30:26.458 --> 30:29.750
CONSCIOUS DENIAL.

30:29.750 --> 30:31.959
BUT THE CASE IS CLOSED.
I'M NOT GONNA PURSUE IT.

30:33.291 --> 30:35.333
BUT I KNEW JAMES.

30:35.333 --> 30:37.834
I KNEW HIM...

30:37.834 --> 30:39.959
AS A PARTNER
AND AS A FRIEND.

30:39.959 --> 30:43.250
AND I HAVE TO KEEP ON BELIEVING
THAT THAT IS WHO HE WAS,

30:43.250 --> 30:46.709
BECAUSE IF HE COULD HIDE
ALL THAT OTHER FUCKED-UP SHIT,

30:46.709 --> 30:49.375
THEN I DON'T THINK
I COULD EVER --

30:49.375 --> 30:51.000
TRUST ANYONE AGAIN.

30:51.000 --> 30:54.709
THAT'S RIGHT.

30:54.709 --> 30:57.875
OR YOURSELF?

31:01.709 --> 31:03.959
I'LL LEAVE A CHECK
IN YOUR OFFICE.

31:12.250 --> 31:15.000
IT'S STRANGE TO HAVE
A CREATION OUT THERE --

31:15.000 --> 31:17.542
A DEEPLY MUTATED VERSION
OF YOURSELF

31:17.542 --> 31:20.125
RUNNING LOOSE
AND SCREWING EVERYTHING UP.

31:20.125 --> 31:22.750
I WONDER IF THIS IS
HOW PARENTS FEEL.

31:28.417 --> 31:29.500
LILA?

31:58.041 --> 31:59.458
LILA?

31:59.458 --> 32:00.709
[ DOOR OPENS ]

32:18.750 --> 32:19.834
[ GASPS ]

32:19.834 --> 32:21.750
WHAT THE FUCK?!

32:22.583 --> 32:23.792
DEX?

32:23.792 --> 32:25.917
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

32:25.917 --> 32:27.750
I CAME TO MAKE SURE
LILA LEFT TOWN.

32:27.750 --> 32:29.834
YEAH, ME TOO.

32:29.834 --> 32:31.375
AND IF SHE WAS STILL HERE,

32:31.375 --> 32:32.792
YOU WERE GONNA WHAT,
WRESTLE HER OUT?

32:32.792 --> 32:34.875
JESUS!

32:34.875 --> 32:37.125
WHAT HAVE WE HERE?

32:38.375 --> 32:41.250
THE DOOR WAS OPEN.

32:41.250 --> 32:45.291
I JUST STEPPED OUT TO BUY
SOME SNACKS FOR THE ROAD TRIP.

32:47.667 --> 32:50.500
COME TO SAY GOODBYE?

32:50.500 --> 32:51.917
[ SCOFFS ]

32:51.917 --> 32:55.125
ACTUALLY, WE CAME TO SEE
THAT YOU CLEARED OUT.

32:55.125 --> 32:57.792
BUT NOW THAT WE SEE
YOU'RE ON YOUR WAY,

32:57.792 --> 33:00.375
WE'RE GOOD TO GO.

33:00.375 --> 33:02.417
HAVE A NICE FUCKING LIFE.

33:10.166 --> 33:12.125
YOU'RE NOT COMING
WITH ME, THEN?

33:12.125 --> 33:13.458
OH, MY GOD.

33:13.458 --> 33:14.959
WHAT DID YOU DO

33:14.959 --> 33:18.291
TO MAKE HER
SO PATHETICALLY CRAZY FOR YOU?

33:18.291 --> 33:19.500
DOES YOUR DICK DANCE?

33:21.083 --> 33:22.875
OH, WELL, OKAY.

33:22.875 --> 33:25.917
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

33:25.917 --> 33:29.667
UM...

33:29.667 --> 33:32.375
I BETTER BE
ON MY WAY, THEN.

33:32.375 --> 33:35.125
UM, I THINK
THAT'S MY BAG.

33:35.125 --> 33:36.834
I MUST HAVE LEFT IT
LAST TIME I WAS HERE.

33:36.834 --> 33:38.333
NO, I'M PRETTY SURE
IT'S MINE.

33:38.333 --> 33:40.542
I CAN OPEN IT UP FOR YOU
IF YOU LIKE,

33:40.542 --> 33:42.291
SO YOU CAN CHECK
FOR YOURSELF.

33:43.500 --> 33:46.667
NO, IT'S MY MISTAKE.

33:46.667 --> 33:49.750
OKAY.

33:49.750 --> 33:51.542
WELL...

33:54.291 --> 33:56.166
...GOODBYE, THEN.

33:56.166 --> 34:00.166
HAVE A NICE FLIGHT.
DON'T FORGET YOUR BROOM.

34:04.709 --> 34:05.875
[ CELLPHONE BEEPING ]

34:05.875 --> 34:07.166
Hello, this is Lila.

34:07.166 --> 34:08.875
Please leave your name
and number,

34:08.875 --> 34:10.792
and I will ring you back
as soon as I can.

34:10.792 --> 34:13.375
LILA, WHERE ARE YOU?
I'M READY TO HIT THE ROAD.

34:13.375 --> 34:16.375
HOPE YOU'RE NOT MAD ABOUT THAT
THING WITH DEB. I HAD TO LIE.

34:16.375 --> 34:19.709
I DON'T WANT HER TO KNOW
WE'RE RUNNING OFF TOGETHER.

34:19.709 --> 34:21.041
CALL ME RIGHT AWAY.

34:21.041 --> 34:22.542
I MISS YOU.

35:01.375 --> 35:02.542
WHAT?

35:12.834 --> 35:15.500
FRANK!

35:15.500 --> 35:17.375
BEDROOM.

35:17.375 --> 35:19.625
"WHAT ARE WE DOING HOME
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE DAY?"

35:19.625 --> 35:22.417
SHE ASKED,
HOPING FOR SEX.

35:24.875 --> 35:29.667
YOU'RE PACKING ALREADY.

35:29.667 --> 35:32.792
GOOD THING
I GOT MY TUQUE.

35:32.792 --> 35:35.000
LAKE IPPERWASH OR BUST.

35:35.000 --> 35:37.375
DEBRA, SLOW DOWN.
OH, WAIT. I GOT A PARKA.

35:37.375 --> 35:40.792
DO YOU KNOW HOW HARD IT IS
TO FIND A PARKA IN MIAMI?

35:40.792 --> 35:42.709
WHEN DO WE LEAVE?

35:42.709 --> 35:45.125
NOT WE. ME.

35:45.125 --> 35:48.291
DEBRA, I JUST GOT A CALL
FROM D.C.

35:48.291 --> 35:52.041
A PATTERN OF BODIES WAS
IDENTIFIED IN OREGON.

35:52.041 --> 35:54.417
MY FLIGHT LEAVES
TONIGHT AT 7:00.

35:54.417 --> 35:57.000
YOU GOT TO BE
FUCKING KIDDING ME.

35:57.000 --> 36:00.583
I WISH I WERE.

36:00.583 --> 36:02.208
BUT IT'S TOO SOON.

36:02.208 --> 36:04.041
I MEAN, IF YOU'RE LEAVING,

36:04.041 --> 36:06.291
WE GOT
TO WORK OUT LOGISTICS.

36:06.291 --> 36:07.917
LOGISTICS?

36:07.917 --> 36:11.041
YEAH, WE GOT A LOT OF SHIT
TO FIGURE OUT --

36:11.041 --> 36:13.917
WEEKEND VISITS
AND RED-EYE FLIGHTS

36:13.917 --> 36:15.250
AND FREQUENT-FLYER PLANS.

36:15.250 --> 36:16.917
LET ME GET MY CALENDAR.

36:16.917 --> 36:18.417
HEY.

36:18.417 --> 36:19.667
HMM?

36:19.667 --> 36:23.208
DO YOU HONESTLY WANT
TO GO DOWN THIS PATH?

36:23.208 --> 36:26.166
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I DON'T.

36:26.166 --> 36:28.000
LONG-DISTANCE RELATIONSHIPS
NEVER WORK OUT,

36:28.000 --> 36:31.000
NOT EVEN IN THE MOVIES.

36:31.000 --> 36:32.208
FUCK IT.

36:34.917 --> 36:36.542
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

36:36.542 --> 36:39.500
LOGISTICS.

36:39.500 --> 36:42.792
I'M TAKING
A LEAVE OF ABSENCE.

36:42.792 --> 36:45.166
YOU'RE NOT
THINKING THIS THROUGH.

36:45.166 --> 36:48.542
WHAT'S TO THINK ABOUT?
I'M GOING WITH YOU.

36:48.542 --> 36:49.959
IT'S JUST A JOB.

36:49.959 --> 36:53.125
IT'S MORE THAN THAT
TO YOU.

36:53.125 --> 36:55.208
OKAY, I LOVE MY JOB,

36:55.208 --> 36:57.375
BUT NOT AS MUCH
AS I LOVE...

37:00.000 --> 37:02.166
...BEING WITH YOU.

37:02.166 --> 37:06.667
JUST DO ME A FAVOR.

37:06.667 --> 37:10.709
TAKE THE AFTERNOON
AND THINK ABOUT THIS.

37:13.458 --> 37:16.333
FINE.

37:16.333 --> 37:17.834
YOU DO ME A FAVOR

37:17.834 --> 37:19.375
AND BUY ME A GODDAMN TICKET
ON YOUR FLIGHT.

37:19.375 --> 37:23.208
I'M GOING HOME TO PACK,
AND I'LL SEE YOU AT THE AIRPORT.

37:37.667 --> 37:39.917
THAT WAS DELICIOUS.

37:39.917 --> 37:41.125
YEAH,
WHAT DID YOU LIKE BETTER,

37:41.125 --> 37:42.792
THE NATURE STEW
OR THE MUD PUDDING?

37:42.792 --> 37:44.041
I WANT WORMS ON TOAST.

37:44.041 --> 37:46.250
CAN WE HAVE WORMS ON TOAST
FOR A SNACK?

37:46.250 --> 37:47.583
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

37:47.583 --> 37:49.291
GO WASH UP, BOTH OF YOU.

37:49.291 --> 37:52.125
HEY, NO RUNNING
IN THE HOUSE, PLEASE.

38:02.500 --> 38:03.959
YEAH, REAL MATURE.

38:05.208 --> 38:06.458
[ GASPS ]

38:11.667 --> 38:13.917
CAPTAIN,
YOU CALLED FOR ME?

38:13.917 --> 38:15.208
OH, HEY, DEXTER.

38:15.208 --> 38:16.500
YEAH, I RECEIVED
A PHONE CALL

38:16.500 --> 38:18.709
FROM A WOMAN THAT SAYS
SHE'S A FRIEND OF YOURS.

38:18.709 --> 38:20.166
WHO?

38:20.166 --> 38:21.375
SHE WOULDN'T
GIVE HER NAME,

38:21.375 --> 38:23.500
BUT CLAIMS TO HAVE
VITAL INFORMATION

38:23.500 --> 38:25.000
ON THE BAY HARBOR BUTCHER.

38:25.000 --> 38:26.500
ANY IDEA WHO SHE MIGHT BE?

38:26.500 --> 38:28.500
ENGLISH ACCENT?
THAT'S HER.

38:28.500 --> 38:33.709
I THINK SHE MIGHT HAVE
A PERSONAL ISSUE WITH ME.

38:33.709 --> 38:36.250
THIS IS THE SAME WOMAN
WHO TRIED TO RAILROAD BATISTA.

38:36.250 --> 38:37.875
YOU MIGHT WANT
TO AVOID HER.

38:37.875 --> 38:39.500
NOT A CHANCE.

38:39.500 --> 38:40.917
NO, THIS CASE IS CLOSING,

38:40.917 --> 38:42.875
AND I CAN'T AFFORD TO LEAVE
ANY LOOSE ENDS.

38:42.875 --> 38:46.250
DID SHE SAY
SHE WAS COMING IN?
WITHIN THE HOUR.

38:46.250 --> 38:50.125
AND YOU SAID
SHE MENTIONED MY NAME?
SPECIFICALLY.

38:50.125 --> 38:51.625
WELL, STICK AROUND.

38:51.625 --> 38:53.458
WE'LL SORT THIS THING OUT
TOGETHER, OKAY?

38:53.458 --> 38:57.458
IF LILA PLANS TO TURN ME IN,

38:57.458 --> 38:59.291
WHY WOULD SHE DROP MY NAME
TO THE CAPTAIN

38:59.291 --> 39:01.000
AND GIVE ME A CHANCE
TO INTERCEPT HER?

39:01.000 --> 39:03.834
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE...

39:03.834 --> 39:07.041
UNLESS SHE WANTS ME HERE SO
SHE CAN HURT ME SOME OTHER WAY.

39:07.041 --> 39:09.375
RITA.

39:20.542 --> 39:22.125
ASTOR?

39:22.125 --> 39:24.667
CODY?

39:24.667 --> 39:26.000
GUYS?!

39:27.250 --> 39:28.375
LEXI.

39:30.166 --> 39:32.333
LEXI!
WHERE ARE THE KIDS?

39:32.333 --> 39:33.750
I CAN'T REMEMBER.

39:33.750 --> 39:37.166
DEXTER,
I GOT YOUR MESSAGE.

39:37.166 --> 39:39.583
WHAT IS IT?
WHAT'S GOING ON?
THE KIDS ARE MISSING.

39:39.583 --> 39:43.166
MISS BENNETT, I AM SO SORRY.
I DIDN'T MEAN TO FALL ASLEEP.

39:43.166 --> 39:44.583
WE HAVE TO CALL
THE POLICE.

39:44.583 --> 39:47.583
CALL DEB. SHE'LL HAVE THE ENTIRE
FORCE LOOKING FOR THEM.

39:47.583 --> 39:49.709
YOU SEE IF ANY OF THE NEIGHBORS
SAW ANYTHING.

39:49.709 --> 39:52.166
I'LL DRIVE AROUND THE AREA.
I PROMISE WE'LL FIND THEM.

39:53.625 --> 39:56.875
WE'RE GOING TO TERMINAL SEVEN --
MIAMI INTERNATIONAL.

39:56.875 --> 40:00.375
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

40:00.375 --> 40:01.667
MORGAN.

40:01.667 --> 40:02.792
DEBRA, IT'S RITA.

40:02.792 --> 40:04.917
HEY, I'M JUST --
I'M GETTING IN A CAB.

40:04.917 --> 40:06.583
LOOK, CODY AND ASTOR
ARE MISSING.

40:06.583 --> 40:08.083
DID YOU CALL THE POLICE?

40:08.083 --> 40:09.166
DEXTER SAID TO CALL YOU.

40:09.166 --> 40:11.709
OKAY, UM,
YOU JUST SIT BY THE PHONE.

40:11.709 --> 40:13.250
I'LL TAKE IT FROM HERE.

40:13.250 --> 40:14.709
ALL RIGHT.

40:14.709 --> 40:17.375
HEY, HOLD UP.
COULD YOU JUST WAIT?

40:17.375 --> 40:20.083
YOU DON'T WANT TO GO
TO THE AIRPORT?

40:20.083 --> 40:21.500
OF COURSE I WANT TO GO
TO THE AIRPORT.

40:21.500 --> 40:23.583
WAIT. I JUST SAID WAIT.

40:23.583 --> 40:26.417
FOR CHRIST'S SAKE,
HONEY, MAKE UP YOUR MIND.

40:26.417 --> 40:29.417
[ Voice breaking ] WHY?

40:29.417 --> 40:32.583
WHY DO I HAVE
TO MAKE UP MY MIND?

40:35.083 --> 40:37.458
GODDAMN IT!

40:37.458 --> 40:38.709
HERE.

40:42.250 --> 40:44.083
Boy: WHOA!

40:44.083 --> 40:46.375
HI, DEXTER.

40:46.375 --> 40:48.917
Boy #2: CAREFUL.
REMEMBER WHAT MOM SAID.

40:48.917 --> 40:50.959
[ CHUCKLES  ]
HI, MOM.

40:50.959 --> 40:53.166
HI, DEXTER.

40:53.166 --> 40:54.291
HEY, DEX.

40:54.291 --> 40:55.583
HEY, GUYS.
YOU HAVING FUN?

40:55.583 --> 40:57.875
SUPER FUN.
LILA'S SO NICE.

40:57.875 --> 40:59.125
WHERE IS LILA?

40:59.125 --> 41:00.583
I'M OVER HERE.

41:04.291 --> 41:05.959
YOU COULD HAVE
HAD IT ALL, DEXTER.

41:18.792 --> 41:20.667
DEXTER!

41:20.667 --> 41:23.250
STAY ON THE BED, GUYS!
DON'T MOVE!

41:31.625 --> 41:33.250
DEXTER!

41:37.083 --> 41:40.083
LOOK AWAY,
BOTH OF YOU.

41:47.041 --> 41:49.041
OKAY, ASTOR, YOU FIRST.

41:49.041 --> 41:51.125
YOU'RE GONNA HELP
YOUR BROTHER.

42:05.166 --> 42:07.041
GO. RUN.
FIND HELP.

42:07.041 --> 42:08.208
COME ON, DEXTER!

42:08.208 --> 42:09.709
I CAN'T FIT.

42:11.375 --> 42:12.834
SHIT.

42:32.125 --> 42:34.667
[ GRUNTING ]

42:37.375 --> 42:39.041
AAH!

42:39.041 --> 42:40.875
[ COUGHING ]

42:43.375 --> 42:45.000
[ GRUNTING ]

42:55.333 --> 42:57.792
WHAT DO YOU REMEMBER
FROM BEFORE --

42:57.792 --> 42:59.875
YOU KNOW,
BEFORE WE TOOK YOU IN?

43:03.375 --> 43:06.083
NOTHING.

43:06.083 --> 43:07.625
GOOD...

43:07.625 --> 43:11.083
BECAUSE WHAT HAPPENED
WAS TOO STRONG.

43:11.083 --> 43:13.333
SON, IT GOT
INTO YOU TOO EARLY,

43:13.333 --> 43:15.333
AND IT'S GONNA STAY THERE.

43:15.333 --> 43:17.709
IT'S GONNA MAKE YOU
WANT TO KILL,

43:17.709 --> 43:20.625
AND YOU WON'T BE ABLE
TO STOP IT.

43:23.542 --> 43:27.750
SO, I'M GOING TO BE
LIKE THIS FOREVER?

43:27.750 --> 43:28.875
YES.

43:39.041 --> 43:40.542
[ GRUNTING ]

43:43.417 --> 43:45.125
[ COUGHING ]

44:04.250 --> 44:05.750
AAH!

44:08.875 --> 44:10.125
AAH.

44:10.125 --> 44:11.625
[ GASPS ]

44:13.959 --> 44:15.875
[ COUGHS ]

44:15.875 --> 44:18.417
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

44:20.208 --> 44:22.750
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.
I GOT YOU.

44:27.542 --> 44:32.959
Woman: NUMBER 1265 TO PARIS
NOW BOARDING AT GATE 5A.

44:39.000 --> 44:40.333
ARRIVING PASSENGERS,

44:40.333 --> 44:43.166
BAGGAGE CLAIM
IS AT GROUND LEVEL.

44:43.166 --> 44:44.542
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

44:50.208 --> 44:51.959
[ POLICE-RADIO CHATTER ]

44:54.375 --> 44:57.333
Dexter: I'M SO SORRY
ABOUT ALL THIS.

44:57.333 --> 44:58.834
IT'S OVER NOW.

44:58.834 --> 45:02.000
THEY'RE SAFE.
YOU'RE SAFE.

45:02.000 --> 45:03.875
THAT'S ALL THAT MATTERS.

45:05.333 --> 45:06.625
COME ON.

45:13.041 --> 45:15.041
YOU TWO,
SECURE A PERIMETER,

45:15.041 --> 45:17.834
AND HAVE THE FIRE CHIEF SEE ME
AS SOON AS HE GETS HERE, OKAY?

45:17.834 --> 45:21.333
PUT OUT AN APB ON LILA WEST,
A.K.A. LILA TOURNAY,

45:21.333 --> 45:23.583
SUSPECTED ARSONIST --

45:23.583 --> 45:26.667
5'7", BLACK HAIR,
PALE LIKE A FUCKING CORPSE.

45:26.667 --> 45:28.375
"FUCKING CORPSE --"
GOT IT.

45:28.375 --> 45:30.208
YOU'RE WASTING
YOUR TIME.

45:30.208 --> 45:32.000
SHE'S NOT COMING BACK --
NOT AFTER THIS.

45:32.000 --> 45:33.250
YEAH,
I WOULDN'T BET ON IT.

45:33.250 --> 45:34.875
SHE WON'T.

45:34.875 --> 45:37.375
SHE'S A SURVIVALIST.

45:37.375 --> 45:39.375
HOW'D YOU KNOW THE KIDS
WERE HERE?

45:39.375 --> 45:42.625
ONE OF THE NEIGHBORS SAW THEM
WALKING WITH A STRANGE WOMAN.

45:42.625 --> 45:44.041
IT WASN'T MUCH OF A LEAP.

45:44.041 --> 45:46.917
LILA'S GONE AFTER EVERYONE
THAT'S CLOSE TO YOU.

45:48.667 --> 45:50.125
WHAT?

45:50.125 --> 45:51.542
IT'S PRETTY IMPRESSIVE.

45:51.542 --> 45:54.667
IT SEEMS IT WASN'T TOO LONG AGO
I WAS TAKING CARE OF YOU.

45:54.667 --> 45:57.750
I LIKE IT BETTER THIS WAY.

45:57.750 --> 45:58.834
YEAH, I CAN SEE THAT.

45:58.834 --> 46:01.875
WHY IS THIS MAN NOT ON THE WAY
TO THE HOSPITAL NOW?

46:01.875 --> 46:03.667
I'M FINE, DEB.

46:03.667 --> 46:07.041
YOU'RE NOT FINE.
YOUR EYEBROWS ARE SINGED.

46:07.041 --> 46:09.792
HOW CAN YOU BE
SO FUCKING RELAXED?

46:12.083 --> 46:15.250
I'M GOOD
AT COMPARTMENTALIZATION.

46:15.250 --> 46:18.458
YOU'RE
A LITTLE WEIRD, DEX.

46:18.458 --> 46:20.041
THAT'S NOT GONNA CHANGE.

46:20.041 --> 46:22.291
I'M GONNA BE
THIS WAY FOREVER.

46:24.208 --> 46:26.208
I CAN LIVE WITH THAT.

46:28.417 --> 46:30.208
JUST SMARTEN UP, OKAY?

46:32.083 --> 46:33.667
Dexter:
I PASSED THROUGH THE FLAMES

46:33.667 --> 46:37.458
AND ROSE FROM THE ASHES...
AGAIN.

46:37.458 --> 46:39.458
I'VE NEVER BEEN ONE
TO PUT MUCH WEIGHT

46:39.458 --> 46:41.125
INTO THE IDEA
OF A HIGHER POWER,

46:41.125 --> 46:43.625
BUT IF I DIDN'T KNOW BETTER,
I'D HAVE TO BELIEVE

46:43.625 --> 46:44.917
THAT SOME FORCE OUT THERE

46:44.917 --> 46:46.959
WANTS ME TO KEEP DOING
WHAT I'M DOING.

47:47.000 --> 47:49.834
[ GASPING ]

47:52.000 --> 47:53.333
DEXTER.

47:53.333 --> 47:55.166
YOU WANTED TO BE
CLOSE TO ME, LILA?

47:55.166 --> 47:57.208
THIS IS THE MOST
I HAVE TO OFFER.

47:57.208 --> 48:01.250
I CAN'T FEEL MY...
LEGS AND MY BODY.

48:01.250 --> 48:02.875
GOOD.

48:02.875 --> 48:05.583
I WENT WITH A SPINAL EPIDURAL
INSTEAD OF THE TRANQUILIZER.

48:05.583 --> 48:06.875
I'VE GOT A PLANE TO CATCH,

48:06.875 --> 48:08.709
AND YOU DON'T NEED
TO FEEL THIS.

48:11.792 --> 48:15.208
YOU KILLED
AN INNOCENT MAN.

48:15.208 --> 48:17.291
I DID IT FOR YOU.

48:17.291 --> 48:18.500
I DID --

48:18.500 --> 48:20.333
DID YOU TRY TO KILL
THE CHILDREN FOR ME, TOO?

48:20.333 --> 48:22.083
[ GROANS ]

48:23.625 --> 48:25.875
DON'T DO THIS.

48:25.875 --> 48:28.208
YOU TAUGHT ME TO ACCEPT
WHAT I AM...

48:30.375 --> 48:33.000
...AND TO TRUST
IN THE ONE THING I KNOW

48:33.000 --> 48:34.333
WITH ABSOLUTE CLARITY.

48:38.417 --> 48:40.125
[ GASPS ]

48:44.458 --> 48:46.125
THANK YOU.

49:03.875 --> 49:06.917
NOT LONG AGO I HAD A DREAM

49:06.917 --> 49:09.250
THAT PEOPLE COULD SEE ME
FOR WHAT I AM,

49:09.250 --> 49:11.083
AND FOR A BRIEF INSTANT
IN TIME,

49:11.083 --> 49:13.583
THE WORLD ACTUALLY SAW
MY BODIES OF WORK.

49:13.583 --> 49:15.208
SOME EVEN CHEERED.

49:15.208 --> 49:18.542
BUT AS IT TURNS OUT,
NOBODY MOURNS THE WICKED.

49:18.542 --> 49:20.583
SORRY, JAMES.

49:23.834 --> 49:26.125
I THINK HARRY KNEW THAT
FROM THE START.

49:26.125 --> 49:27.709
THAT'S WHY HE GAVE ME A CODE.

49:27.709 --> 49:29.125
IT COST HIM HIS LIFE,

49:29.125 --> 49:32.166
BUT IT KEPT ME ALIVE
THROUGH INCREDIBLE TRIALS.

49:32.166 --> 49:34.959
THE CODE IS MINE NOW
AND MINE ALONE.

49:34.959 --> 49:37.625
SO, TOO, ARE THE RELATIONSHIPS
I CULTIVATE.

49:44.041 --> 49:47.083
THEY'RE NOT
JUST DISGUISES ANYMORE.

49:47.083 --> 49:49.083
I NEED THEM...

49:49.083 --> 49:51.959
EVEN IF
THEY MAKE ME VULNERABLE.

49:51.959 --> 49:56.667
MY FATHER MIGHT NOT APPROVE,
BUT I'M NO LONGER HIS DISCIPLE.

49:56.667 --> 49:58.959
I'M A MASTER NOW...

49:58.959 --> 50:02.000
AN IDEA TRANSCENDED INTO LIFE.

50:06.709 --> 50:09.208
AND SO THIS IS MY NEW PATH,

50:09.208 --> 50:11.417
WHICH IS A LOT LIKE
THE OLD ONE...

50:11.417 --> 50:14.625
ONLY MINE.

50:14.625 --> 50:17.333
TO STAY ON THAT PATH,
I NEED TO WORK HARDER,

50:17.333 --> 50:20.041
EXPLORE NEW RITUALS,
EVOLVE.

50:22.500 --> 50:25.750
AM I EVIL? AM I GOOD?

50:25.750 --> 50:28.166
I'M DONE ASKING
THOSE QUESTIONS.

50:28.166 --> 50:31.583
I DON'T HAVE THE ANSWERS.

50:31.583 --> 50:33.458
DOES ANYONE?

50:38.166 --> 50:46.208
